eeker:]&lt;br&gt;\n&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/=\r\nb&gt;Why the fate is so harsh? Why even good people have to suffer? What is\nth=\r\ne cause for fate? What is the rule behind it, to manifest? What is the caus=\r\ne\nfor happiness and misery?&lt;br&gt;\n&lt;b&gt;&lt;u&gt;&lt;span style=3D&#39;color:black&#39;&gt;[Kannan:]=\r\n&lt;br&gt;\n&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;span style=3D&#39;color:black&#39;&gt;I appreciate your question =\r\nvery much,\nand I would take delight in answering it.&lt;br&gt;\nYou are focused on=\r\n &#8220;cause-effect&#8221; relationship. In this case, every &#8220;event&=\r\n#8221;\nwhich occurs needs a &#8220;precedence&#8221; or &#8221;pre-event&#8=\r\n221; or &#8220; synchronous co-event&#8221;\ncalled as &#8220;cause&#8221;. =\r\nThis will happen if the &lt;b&gt;progression&lt;/b&gt; of Kaala is\neither linear or cir=\r\ncular. In fact, a small arc of a circle is just a line. So\nlinear and circu=\r\nlar are technically called 1-Dimensional geometrical entity\ncalled &#8220;l=\r\nine&#8221;; with the only difference being that a line segment has differen=\r\nt\nstarting point and end point, whereas a circular line segment(also called=\r\n arc)\nhas same starting and ending point.&lt;br&gt;\n&lt;br&gt;\nNow in order to answer y=\r\nour question, this adherence to &#8220;cause-effect&#8221; will not\nhelp. B=\r\necause, your question is even beyond this. Your question is a deeply\nphilos=\r\nophical one. But the answer is there.&lt;br&gt;\n&lt;br&gt;\nNow, from the perspective of=\r\n Truth or Ultimate Reality or ParaBrahman or Self\nor Aatmaa or Supreme Bein=\r\ng, there is no space, no time, no progression, no\ncause-effect. It just exi=\r\nsts, and nothing else exists.Thus it is &#8220;Sat&#8221;.&lt;br&gt;\n&lt;br&gt;\nNow lis=\r\nten carefully. This Aatma has a &#8220;center of desire&#8221; or &#8220;va=\r\nasnaa-kendra&#8221;\ncalled &#8220;Chitta&#8221;. This &#8220;Chitta&#8221; =\r\nis also a permanent nature of Aatma just like\n&#8220;Sat&#8221;. &nbsp;&#82=\r\n20;Sat&#8221; is its continued ever-lasting existence. Thus the Aatma\ndwell=\r\ns in &#8220;Sat&#8221; and &#8220;Chitta&#8221;, and hence is called &#8220=\r\n;Sat-Chitt-Aananda&#8221;, meaning\none who dwells in &#8220;Sat&#8221; and =\r\n&#8220;Chitta&#8221;, blissfully.&lt;br&gt;\n&nbsp;Aum Shri Satchittaanda Parabrah=\r\nma Purushottama Paramaatma.&lt;br&gt;\n&lt;br&gt;\nNow, This Aatmaa always exist in eithe=\r\nr of one of the following states or\n&#8220;awastha&#8221; called jaagruta(w=\r\naking), swapna(dreaming), sushupta(sleeping), and\nturiya(moksha); just like=\r\n an ordinary human being sleeps, dreams and is awake,\nbut he exists in all =\r\nthe 3 states, witnessing each and all of them.&lt;br&gt;\n&lt;br&gt;\nJust like Aatma is =\r\nShaaswatam(ever-existing) likewise its witnessing of each of\nthese states i=\r\ns also Shaashwatam. Means, it is always, at any given instant,\nfound witnes=\r\nsing one of these states.&lt;br&gt;\n&lt;br&gt;\n&lt;b&gt;The Chitta of Aatma is the centre of =\r\ndesires. All these states are in Chitta\nonly except turiya. An Aatma as &#8=\r\n220;Sat&#8221; is in Turiya state. But An aatma as\n&#8221;Chitta&#8221; is =\r\nwitnessing one of the other three states namely, Jaagruta, Swapna\nand Sushu=\r\npti. I hope this line very well summarises the whole point.&lt;/b&gt;&lt;br&gt;\n&lt;br&gt;\nNo=\r\nw, this Jaagruta or Waking state of Aatma is called &#8220;Srushti&#8221; o=\r\nr &#8220;Creation&#8221;\nor &#8220;World&#8221; or &#8220;Brahmanda&#8221; =\r\nor &#8220;Cosmos&#8221; which is visibly manifested and\nwitnessed. This is =\r\nDay.&lt;br&gt;\nThe Sushupti or Sleeping state of Aatma is the &#8220;pralaya&#822=\r\n1; or &#8220;dissolution&#8221;. This\nis Night.&lt;br&gt;\n&lt;br&gt;\nAnd this cycle of =\r\nAatma keeps repeating again and again, permanently,\neverlastingly. Just lik=\r\ne aatma is nitya(everlasting) and satya(Truth), this\nrepetition of cycle of=\r\n waking and sleeping is also nitya and satya means\neverlasting and truth.&lt;b=\r\nr&gt;\n&lt;br&gt;\nSwapna is not an independent stable state, rather it is a transitio=\r\nn state from\nwaking to sleeping or from sleeping to waking.&lt;br&gt;\n&lt;br&gt;\nThis i=\r\ns why the Aatma is expressed in word as &#8220;AUM&#8230;.&#8221;. &lt;br&gt;\nA &=\r\n#8211; jaagruta or srushti or creation&lt;br&gt;\nM- sushupti or nidra or pralaya =\r\nor sleeping state.&lt;br&gt;\nU- transition.&lt;br&gt;\n&lt;br&gt;\nIf you open your mouth to sa=\r\ny &#8220;A&#8221;, then its creation. If you close your lips to\nsay &#8220;=\r\nM&#8221;, its dissolution, and &#8220;U&#8221; is the transition that you e=\r\nxperience while\nshuttling between A and M.&lt;br&gt;\nThe brief reverberating sile=\r\nnce just after AUM is Turiya.&lt;br&gt;\n&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br&gt;\nNow, Aatmaa is also called &#=\r\n8220;chaitanya&#8221; or &#8220;consciousness&#8221; or &#8220;awareness&#8=\r\n221; or\n&#8220;existence&#8221;.&lt;br&gt;\n&lt;span style=3D&#39;color:black&#39;&gt;&lt;br&gt;\nHavin=\r\ng said upto this, the answer is slowly revealing now. The chitta is a\ncolle=\r\nction of vrittis or shades of desires, which seek to manifest. Every\nindivi=\r\ndual is Aatma whose chitta has manifested its vrittis and manifested as a\nl=\r\nifetime. There are many latent vrittis hidden in chitta yet unmanifested. T=\r\nhis\nis what is called &#8220;karmic sediments&#8221;.&lt;br&gt;\n&lt;br&gt;\nJust like Aa=\r\ntma is ever-lasting ,this chitta is also everlasting and with every\nlifetim=\r\ne, new vrittis are continuously created every moment, and at the same\ntime =\r\nold vrittis keep manifesting.&lt;br&gt;\n&lt;br&gt;\nJyotisha Vidya is all about studying=\r\n the surya-mandala, so as to understand\nwhich vritti is going to manifest i=\r\nn this given space and time interval on\nearth, in this lifetime.&lt;br&gt;\n&lt;br&gt;\nT=\r\nhrough remedies, the vritti that is about to manifest can be nulled and bur=\r\nnt\nat its very core, and thus blocking it from manifesting. But this requir=\r\nes a\nhigher level of awareness. &lt;br&gt;\n&lt;br&gt;\nThe reason for misery is ignoranc=\r\ne(avidya), wrong identity of the self with\nsomething else, unable to digest=\r\n manifesting vrittis going against one&#8217;s own\nagenda.&lt;br&gt;\n&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br&gt;\n=\r\n&lt;span style=3D&#39;color:black&#39;&gt;Dear Everyone,&lt;br&gt;\nThe post is getting longer b=\r\nut the subject is too involved. I hope I have\nfairly approached closer in a=\r\nnswering you, if not answered you completely to\nyour satisfaction.&lt;br&gt;\nWe w=\r\nill see more later. Thank You.&lt;br&gt;\n&lt;br&gt;\nWith Kind Regards,&lt;br&gt;\nKannan&lt;/span=\r\n&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;o:p&gt;&lt;/o:p&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\n\n&lt;/div&gt;\n\n&lt;/body&gt;\n\n&lt;/html&gt;\n\r\n------=_NextPart_000_0041_01CF40B2.FC9DCC70--\r\n\n"}}